The paper deals with the compression of context-free grammars, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of algebraic circuits and finite base properties suggests a connection to complexity theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents results on tree compression, which could also place it in the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
